When you hit rock bottom, you have to dig deep to find the strength to keep moving forward. Everything I’ve done with the best of intentions has blown up in my face. Everything I touch turns to ash. Every relationship I’ve built is shredded and I just can’t catch a break in the game. 

My allies have turned on me, my friends turned on me and I’ve burnt or been burnt by every single player left in this game in one shape or another. Everything I do and say is now questioned with a cloud of doubt. 

I have no control, no agency and no friends right now. And I can’t describe just how lonely and depressing that feeling is. 

But I’m still here. I’m not dead yet. And this lost puppy is not ready to be put down. When the whole world is against you, do you have the strength to get back up and go another round? Time to find out. 👊🏽

7.30 tonight on 10 and 10 play. 
@survivorau #survivorau

I MADE IT TO MERGE! 🥹🥹🥹

What a difference 24 hours makes in this game. This lone wolf has found a pack 🐺

So far down the pecking order I’m not even pecking, living on the bottom since day 16, I’ve flipped 4 times on the people I’ve been working with, swimming with the sharks, completely out of the loop and I am the only remaining player in this game with 0 votes against them at Tribal Council. CAN SOMEONE PLEASE TELL ME WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON? 😭🙃
 
But in all seriousness I came into merge and thought that maybe the best thing for me was to stay on the bottom, I could surrender all control and agency to extinguish my threat level for a few more days in the game. And something seems to be working out for me with a few well times necklaces. One day at a time. Let’s go! 
 
7.30 tonight on 10 and 10play @survivorau #survivorau

Omg. OMG. Are you kidding me 😱
 
This game works in mysterious ways and has delivered me some of the highest highs and the lowest lows. But this is one high that I will never forget…
 
I JUST WON A BRAND NEW ISUZU D-MAX! ‘THE BEAST’ 🛻
 
As an apprentice carpenter on minimum wage, this D-Max will help change my life. Thank you! This is one happy little Chippy! 
 
I’m sure you can recall the @isuzuute_aus tagline. GO YOUR OWN WAY. And I feel there are so many parallels to my own game. I stand up for what I believe in, I wear my heart on my sleeve and I’m playing the game my own way (and whilst it hasn’t been conventional, I’m still here in the final 7) and of course… enjoying every moment of the journey. 
 
So here’s to making the most of every moment and enjoying the ride. It ain’t over yet.

Snuff’d!!! What a ride. What an absolute ride. 

I love this game and everything about it. I came to Samoa for redemption and to leave my mark on the game of Survivor. I achieved so much more than I ever could have dreamed of and I did it in a way which I never thought was possible.

42 days
27 days on the bottom
Top 6 finish
4 Individual Immunity Necklaces 
1 New Isuzu D-Max
A merge buff 😍
Some lifelong memories and new friends 

To everyone who has been in my corner, everyone who bought a Snuff’d hat, anyone who has flicked me a message, cheered me on from the couch, screamed through their TV screen in support… especially through the tough times, thank you. To my friends and family, thanks for joining me on the roller coaster. And to my wife @bec__kate, thank you for your love and support. 

In the game of survivor, you either die a villain or you live long enough to see yourself become a h… a goofball with a dream and a fake cookie idol who never gave up 🍪🤷🏻‍♂️

Good luck to the Final 5 ❤️

Big love
Simon

I set out to beat my batting all time high score of 12, set back in 2002 with the mighty Under 12 C’s. Turns out I’ve still got it. Equaling my record of 12 before @danhunj bowled me out, middle stump 👏🏽

All of our signed shirts are available to bid on at Llyod’s Auctions with all funds going to the @markhughesfoundation check it out now to support a good cause. I’ll throw in a signed @snuffd.apparel hat for the winning bid. 

For the record we won by 5 runs, and beat the MAFS boys. Thanks for having me @celebritybigbash!

PS. Definitely could have scored 13 if Heals had of been a bit faster between the stumps… just saying 😂 Although he did go on to high score for our winning team.

Finally getting around to fixing up the backyard 🏡

When we pulled out the jungle in the back yard, behind it we found the old fence had rotten out, fallen over and was over due for the Colorbond treatment. 

I was debating whether to drop in the posts at correct height, or run them long and cut them back. Running them long was the right choice for this job, easy to get the top rails perfectly level and tweak the fence height after the sleepers went into the ground. I was also tossing up about the best way to cut the posts down, whilst avoiding grinders and cutting discs on the Colorbond, but I picked up a @makitaaustralia metal cut saw DCS553Z from @totaltoolsaustralia and it chewed through it like butter 🧈

12m down at the back. Now 24m down the side to go. This is going to look 👌🏽 once the turf goes down!
